Trim and halve the @green beans{80%grams}. Drain the @king prawns{225%grams}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the prawns and beans to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir-fry the prawns for ~{4-5%minutes}. Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns. Cook so they're opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the prawns are cooked, add the garlic and @coleslaw mix{120%grams}. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @udon noodles{220%grams} to the pan. Toss to coat, using a #fork{} to gently separate them.

Simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @ketjap manis{50%grams}, @soy sauce{15%ml} and @honey{15%grams} to the noodles.

Toss together so everything's evenly coated in the sauce.

Stir-fry until piping hot, ~{1%minute}. Add a splash of @water{splash} if you feel it needs it. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Share the noodles between your serving #bowls{} and drizzle over the @hot sauce{30%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) to finish. Enjoy!